---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="Getting Started">

  <section class="gs-intro">
    <p class="gs-eyebrow">Setup Guide</p>
    <h1 class="gs-h1">Getting started</h1>
    <p class="gs-summary">
      The UX Intelligence agents run inside <strong>Claude Code</strong> — a command-line tool
      that connects Claude directly to this repository. You'll need a GitHub account with access
      to the repo, and Claude Code installed on your machine. This guide walks you through both.
    </p>
    <div class="gs-notice">
      <strong>Why Claude Code, not Claude.ai?</strong>
      Claude.ai can trigger the agents and read pages, but it can't write files to this
      repository — so reports won't be saved and screenshots won't be committed. Claude Code
      runs inside the repo on your machine, which is what gives it permission to create files,
      commit screenshots, and push the finished report to the site.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 1: GitHub account ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">1</span>
      Create a GitHub account
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      If you don't already have one, sign up for a free GitHub account. You'll need this to
      request access to the repo.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/signup" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-external-link">
      <span class="gs-external-icon">↗</span>
      github.com/signup
    </a>
    <p class="gs-body gs-body--note">
      Use your THG work email address when signing up so it's easy for the repo admin to verify
      who you are when granting access.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 2: Repo access ───────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">2</span>
      Request access to the repository
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      The repository is private. Once you have a GitHub account, ask David Jones
      (<code>@davidedwardjones18</code> on GitHub) to add you as a collaborator. Share your
      GitHub username and he'll send an invite.
    </p>
    <div class="gs-repo-card">
      <div class="gs-repo-header">
        <span class="gs-repo-icon">◈</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-repo-org">THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds</p>
          <p class="gs-repo-name">ux-prototyping</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="gs-repo-desc">
        The UX Intelligence site and all agent-generated reports. Private — requires an invite.
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-repo-link">
        View on GitHub →
      </a>
    </div>
    <p class="gs-body gs-body--note">
      Once you accept the invite, you'll have <strong>write access</strong> — needed so Claude
      Code can push new report pages and screenshots to the repo on your behalf.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 3: Clone the repo ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">3</span>
      Clone the repository
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Once you have access, clone the repo to your machine. Open a terminal and run:
    </p>
    <pre class="gs-code">git clone https://github.com/THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping.git
cd ux-prototyping</pre>
    <p class="gs-body">
      If you're prompted for GitHub credentials, use a
      <a href="https://github.com/settings/tokens" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-inline-link">personal access token</a>
      rather than your password — GitHub no longer accepts passwords over HTTPS. Set the token
      scope to <code>repo</code> (full control of private repositories).
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 4: Install Claude Code ───────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">4</span>
      Install Claude Code
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Claude Code is a CLI tool that runs Claude inside your terminal, with access to your local
      files and git. Install it via npm:
    </p>
    <pre class="gs-code">npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</pre>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Once installed, authenticate with your Anthropic account:
    </p>
    <pre class="gs-code">claude</pre>
    <p class="gs-body">
      This opens a browser window to log in. Use your work Anthropic account if the team has
      one, or your personal account if you're on an individual plan. If you don't have an
      Anthropic account yet, sign up at
      <a href="https://claude.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-inline-link">claude.ai</a>
      — a Pro plan ($20/month) is sufficient for running the agents.
    </p>
    <a href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/getting-started" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-external-link">
      <span class="gs-external-icon">↗</span>
      Claude Code — official getting started docs
    </a>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 5: Open the repo in Claude Code ─────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">5</span>
      Open the repo in Claude Code
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Navigate to the cloned repo in your terminal and launch Claude Code:
    </p>
    <pre class="gs-code">cd ux-prototyping
claude</pre>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Claude Code starts in the context of this repository. The agents are already installed
      as skills — you'll see them available as slash commands. You're now ready to run your
      first report.
    </p>
    <div class="gs-tip">
      <strong>Check the agents are available.</strong>
      Type <code>/</code> in the Claude Code prompt to see the list of available slash commands.
      You should see <code>/myprotein-ux-review</code>, <code>/competitor-analysis</code>,
      <code>/design-qa</code>, and <code>/myprotein-prep-agent</code> in the list.
      If they're missing, run <code>/setup-cowork</code> to install the skills.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 6: Run your first report ─────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">6</span>
      Run your first report
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      With Claude Code open inside the repo, trigger the UX Review agent with a URL:
    </p>
    <pre class="gs-code">/myprotein-ux-review https://www.myprotein.com/sports-nutrition/impact-whey-protein/10530943.html</pre>
    <p class="gs-body">
      The agent will navigate to the page, take screenshots, analyse the UX, and write a report
      file. When it's done, commit and push the output:
    </p>
    <pre class="gs-code">git add src/pages/reports/ src/assets/reports/
git commit -m "Add UX review: Impact Whey PDP (2026-06-08)"
git push</pre>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Vercel picks up the push and redeploys automatically — the report is live within a couple
      of minutes. See the individual
      <a href="/#agents" class="gs-inline-link">agent guides</a>
      for the full step-by-step walkthrough for each agent type.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Troubleshooting ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">Common setup issues</h2>
    <ul class="gs-tips-list">
      <li>
        <strong><code>git push</code> asks for a username and password.</strong>
        GitHub no longer accepts account passwords over HTTPS. Go to
        <a href="https://github.com/settings/tokens/new" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-inline-link">github.com/settings/tokens/new</a>,
        generate a token with <code>repo</code> scope, and use that as your password. Store it
        in your macOS Keychain so you're not prompted again.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Claude Code says "authentication required" or "no API key".</strong>
        Run <code>claude auth</code> in your terminal to re-authenticate. If you're on a team
        plan, ask David for the shared API key and set it with
        <code>export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-key</code> in your shell profile.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Slash commands aren't showing up.</strong>
        The skills need to be installed. Run <code>/setup-cowork</code> from inside the Claude
        Code prompt and follow the prompts. This installs the agent skills into your Claude Code
        session.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Can I use Claude.ai instead of Claude Code?</strong>
        For reading and analysing pages, yes. But Claude.ai can't write files to this repo or
        push commits — so the report won't be saved and screenshots won't appear on the site.
        For anything that produces a report, use Claude Code.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>I cloned the repo but <code>npm run dev</code> doesn't work.</strong>
        The local dev server is only needed if you're editing the site itself. You don't need it
        to run the agents — Claude Code only needs the repo files, not a running server. If you
        do want the dev server, run <code>npm install</code> first to pull in dependencies.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Quick links ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">Quick links</h2>
    <div class="gs-links-grid">
      <a href="https://github.com/THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">◈</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">GitHub repository</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/getting-started" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">⌘</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">Claude Code docs</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">Installation, authentication, commands</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/settings/tokens/new" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">⚿</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">GitHub personal access token</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">Create a token with repo scope</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/agents/ux-review" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">↗</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">Agent guides</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">Step-by-step for each agent</p>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .gs-intro {
    margin-bottom: 52px;
  }
  .gs-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .gs-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .gs-summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .gs-notice {
    background: #FFF8E1;
    border: 1px solid rgba(230, 81, 0, 0.2);
    border-left: 4px solid #E65100;
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .gs-notice strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #BF360C;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  /* ── Sections ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .gs-section {
    margin-bottom: 52px;
  }
  .gs-section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    padding-bottom: 12px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .gs-step-badge {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 800;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .gs-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .gs-body--note {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  .gs-inline-link {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .gs-inline-link:hover { opacity: 0.75; }

  /* ── Code blocks ────────────────────────────────────────── */
  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .gs-code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    white-space: pre;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  /* ── External link pill ─────────────────────────────────── */
  .gs-external-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: 99px;
    padding: 7px 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    transition: box-shadow 0.15s, transform 0.1s;
  }
  .gs-external-link:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(0,57,66,0.1);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .gs-external-icon {
    font-size: 14px;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  /* ── Repo card ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .gs-repo-card {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 20px 22px;
    max-width: 480px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .gs-repo-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .gs-repo-icon {
    font-size: 24px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .gs-repo-org {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }
  .gs-repo-name {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .gs-repo-desc {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }
  .gs-repo-link {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .gs-repo-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  /* ── Tip box ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .gs-tip {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 14px 18px;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .gs-tip strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  /* ── Tips list ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .gs-tips-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 14px;
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .gs-tips-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 14px 18px;
  }
  .gs-tips-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  /* ── Quick links grid ───────────────────────────────────── */
  .gs-links-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .gs-link-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 14px;
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 16px 18px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: box-shadow 0.15s, transform 0.1s, border-color 0.15s;
  }
  .gs-link-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,57,66,0.09);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: rgba(0,57,66,0.25);
  }
  .gs-link-icon {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 1px;
  }
  .gs-link-title {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .gs-link-sub {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    opacity: 0.65;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
</style>
